The Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) in Kebbi says it has deployed 864 personnel, 10 patrol vehicles and five ambulances across the state to ensure hitch-free Yuletide celebrations. Mr Abayomi Asaniyan, the FRSC Sector Commander in the state, disclose this to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Monday in Birnin Kebbi. He said that the command had set up three Emergency Rescue Services Camps along designated routes in Kalgo, Ambursa and Keri-Koko as part of measures to ensure sanity on the state roads. “In pursuance to the commitment of realising our corporate mandate and ensure highways and roads are safer during the yuletide, we have mobilised 864 personnel including special Marshals and NYSC members. “We have also deployed 10 patrol vehicles, five ambulances and three emergency rescue services camps along designated routes in Kalgo, Ambursa and Keri-Koko. “These are measures to ensure sanity on the state roads during this year’s Christmas and end of the year celebrations,’’ the sector commander said. He said that the camp would give immediate attention to crash victims, while at the same time reduce fatalities. Asaniyan said that FRSC also deployed an advanced life support ambulance, a heavy duty tow truck, breathalyzers for testing drivers for drugs and alcohol consumption and extricating machines. He said the commission would work in synergy with other relevant sister agencies to ensure the highways were safe for all users. The sector commander appealed to motorists to show consideration to other road users and obey all traffic rules and regulations. (NAN).